Now that the unions have settled for Eskom’s  offer, after wrecking the country without any consequences, where does Eskom get the money to pay the increases? André de  Ruyter is not allowed to retrench the “duplicates” on the workforce who were paid in full during Covid, so the only place  to retrieve the 7% needed is from the few who pay for electricity. These are the same few who have  received no increases over the past two years,  owing to Covid, or   who got meagre increases well below 7%, or   used all their savings to survive or save their businesses. Bite the hand that feeds you, and that hand will no longer feed you.   Peter Gordon GrantSedgefield The FM welcomes concise letters from readers. They can be sent to fmmail@fm.co.za